    "body": "@zcbenz \nI forgot a key point(this bug only occur when setSize(screenSize.width, screenSize.height) and source size are (screenSize.width, screenSize.height))\nIn the previous example code, BrowserWindow's initial width and height are (800,600),but in my code,they are (screenSize.width, screenSize.height) and it not working corrently(only display at clientarea of desktop),so I add `win.setSize(screenSize.width, screenSize.height);`,and the bug appear.\n(The following is a minimum app that reproduces this bug)\n\n```\nconst electron = require('electron');\nconst app = electron.app;\nconst BrowserWindow = electron.BrowserWindow;\nlet mainWindow = null;\napp.on('window-all-closed', function() {\n    app.quit();\n});\n\napp.on('ready', function() {\n    let screenSize = electron.screen.getPrimaryDisplay().size;\n    mainWindow = new BrowserWindow({\n        width: screenSize.width,\n        height: screenSize.height,\n        enableLargerThanScreen: true,\n        show: false,\n        transparent: true,\n        frame: false,\n        resizable: false,\n        skipTaskbar: true\n    });\n    mainWindow.loadURL('http://github.com');\n    mainWindow.setSkipTaskbar(true);\n    mainWindow.setSize(screenSize.width, screenSize.height);\n    mainWindow.show();\n});\n```\n\nQ:Why you dont use full-screen window directly? A: Full-screen window couldn't be transparent ...\n"
